·	Knowledge of the basic hazard and risk assessment techniques.
·	Knowledge to select and use proper personal protective equipment.
·	Understanding of the basic hazardous materials terms.
·	Knowledge to perform basic control, containment and/or confinement operations within the capabilities of the resources and personal protective equipment provided to the First Responder Operations Level.
·	Knowledge to implement basic decontamination procedures.
·	Understanding of the relevant standard operating procedures and termination procedures.

Hazardous Materials Technicians will receive a minimum of 24 hours of training equal to the First Responder Operations Level.  Annual refresher training is required in the following:

·	Implementation of the employer¿s emergency response plan;
·	Usage of field survey instruments and equipment to classify, to identify and to verify known and unknown materials;
·	Function within an assigned role in the Incident Command System;
·	Selection and usage of proper specialized chemical personal protective equipment provided to the Hazardous Materials Technician;
·	Hazard and risk assessment techniques;
·	Advance control, containment and/or confinement operations within the capabilities of the resources and personal protective equipment available with the unit;
·	Decontamination procedures;
·	Termination procedures;
·	Basic chemical and toxicological terminology and behavior; and
·	Function as Site liaison with federal, state, local or other government authorities in regards to Site activities.

